      "level": {
        "value": 7
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>The Skoan-Quah ambassador</strong> — aged Skull Clan shaman who spent years in Korvosa keeping the peace and watching the old tombs in the city's bedrock. His grandson Gaekhen's murder (Ch.1) and Ileosa's coronation send him home to the Kallow Mounds — where, if the PCs honored Gaekhen, he becomes the door to everything in Ch.4.</p><p><strong>Tactics:</strong> heals and wards from the rear; prefers words to war. <strong>Morale:</strong> never leaves while one ally still fights; alone, he surrenders to honorable foes and trusts the spirit world with the rest.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
